### Implementation Details (JavaScript)

We will use regular expressions for easy tokenization of letter sequences.

If $s = "a--b a--c"$.
Regex `/[a-z]+/g` applied to $s$:
1. Finds "a"
2. Skips "--" (not letters)
3. Finds "b"
4. Skips " "
5. Finds "a"
6. Skips "--"
7. Finds "c"

