Let's write the code structure.
Since the constraints are large ($10^5$), string manipulation needs to be efficient, which regex replacement/matching generally is.

```javascript
function solve(chunks, queries) {
    // 1. Concatenate chunks
    const s = chunks.join('');

    // 2. Initialize word counts
    const wordCounts = new Map();

    // 3. Find all maximal contiguous sequences of letters (Words)
    // Regex /[a-z]+/g finds all sequences of one or more lowercase letters.
    const matches = s.match(/[a-z]+/g);

    if (matches) {
        // 4. Count occurrences
        for (const word of matches) {
            wordCounts.set(word, (wordCounts.get(word) || 0) + 1);
        }
    }

    // 5. Generate result array
    const ans = [];
    for (const query of queries) {
        // 6. Lookup count
        const count = wordCounts.get(query) || 0;
        ans.push(count);
    }

    return ans;
}
```

